## Icons

- Always use icons from the `@design-systems/icons` package
- For icon usage guidelines, installation, props, and best practices, refer to the `icons` rule
- Import by name: `import { IconName } from '@design-systems/icons'`
- Always verify icon exists before using it
- Never hardcode inline SVGs unless the icon doesn't exist in the design system

## Design Tokens

- Always use design system tokens for colors, spacing, typography, etc.
- Reference tokens as CSS variables: `var(--color-action-standard)`, `var(--space-medium)`, etc.
- For an overview of all available token categories, refer to the `tokens` rule
- For specific token values, read the category-specific rules (e.g., `tokens-color`, `tokens-space`)
- When using Figma designs, validate tokens exist in the token rules before using them
- Never hardcode values that have corresponding design tokens

## Code Examples

### Good Example - Using Design System Components

```tsx
// Page component â€” import path is relative from src/pages/
import styles from '../styles/[Name].module.css'

function App() {
  return (
    <div className={styles.appContainer}>
      <header className={styles.header}>
        <h1 className={styles.brandText}>Title</h1>
        <Button priority="primary">Action</Button>
      </header>
      <main className={styles.mainContent}>
        <div className={styles.card}>
          <Typography variant="heading-6">Section</Typography>
          <Badge status="success">Complete</Badge>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  )
}
```

### Good Example - Using Design Tokens

```css
.appContainer {
  padding: var(--space-container-padding-medium);
  background: var(--color-page-background-secondary);
  font-family: var(--font-family-body);
}

.header {
  background: var(--color-container-background-primary);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-divider-tertiary);
}

.brandText {
  font-size: var(--font-size-heading-6);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-heading-bold);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
}

/* Responsive */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .appContainer {
    padding: var(--space-container-padding-small);
  }
}
```

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

1. Using CSS-in-JS (styled-components, emotion) - use CSS Modules instead
2. Hardcoding colors instead of using tokens
3. Creating wrapper components around design system components
4. Using absolute positioning for layouts
5. Importing inline SVGs instead of using @design-systems/icons
6. Forgetting to import component CSS files
7. Not testing responsive design on mobile/tablet/desktop

## Success Checklist

Before considering implementation complete, verify:

- [ ] All components use @ids-ts/* packages when possible
- [ ] All colors, spacing, and typography use design tokens
- [ ] Component CSS files are imported alongside component imports
- [ ] Icons come from @design-systems/icons (no inline SVGs or third-party libraries)
- [ ] Proper semantic HTML structure with accessible markup

## When to Ask Questions

Ask for clarification if:
1. The design uses a component type not available in @ids-ts/*
2. The design requires custom styling beyond design tokens
3. The design isn't pixel-perfect after initial implementation
4. Multiple responsive states are shown (desktop vs mobile)